CaseSummary.Summary: Vehicle one (V1 - case vehicle), a 2004 Chevrolet Aveo, 5-door hatchback was traveling west in the westbound lane of a two-lane, two-way, rural roadway. Vehicle two (V2), a 2001 Chevrolet Malibu, 4-door sedan was also traveling west in the westbound lane and was ahead of V1. Vehicle three (V3), a 1999 GMC Sierra K1500, 2-door pickup truck pulling a utility trailer was traveling east in the eastbound lane of the same roadway. It was daylight, raining, and the bituminous road was wet. The driver of V1 reported that he suddenly recognized that V2 was in front of him and he attempted to avoid V2 by steering to the left, but the right side of V1 struck the rear corner of V2. The driver of V3 saw V1 enter the eastbound lane and attempted to avoid a collision by steering to the right. V3 was partially off the road but the front of V1 struck the left side of V3's utility trailer. V1 was towed due to disabling vehicle damage. V2 and V3 were both driven from the scene, but V3's utility trailer was reportedly obliterated. The 63-year-old male driver of V1 (case occupant) was not using the available three-point seat belt but the steering-wheel airbag deployed. He was transported via ground ambulance to a regional level-one trauma center.

CirenCaseForm.InjuryAnalysis:
The case occupant is the 188 cm (6' 2"), 94 kg (207 lb), 63-year-old male driver of a 2004 Chevrolet Aveo, 5-door hatchback that swerved out of its lane to avoid striking a 2001 Chevrolet Malibu, 4-door sedan in the rear. The right side of the case vehicle sideswiped the rear corner of the Malibu. The front of the case vehicle then struck the left side of a utility trailer being pulled by a 1999 GMC Sierra K1500, 2-door pickup that had swerved to the right to avoid the case vehicle. The initial impact was classified as minor, and no WinSmash reconstruction was attempted due to the sideswipe nature of the collision. The second impact was classified as moderate. The WinSmash reconstruction program calculated an equivalent barrier speed of 15 kmph (9 mph), which appeared to be consistent with the observed vehicle damage. The case occupant was not using the available three-point seat belt. The steering wheel airbag deployed.
He sustained a loss of consciousness and a left parietal scalp contusion probably from contact with flying debris (wooden side rails on metal frame) from the struck wooden utility trailer. He sustained five right rib fractures (#4-8 antero-lateral) from contact with the steering-wheel airbag. He sustained a moderate liver laceration from contact with the steering wheel through the airbag. He sustained fractures of the left humeral neck and left olecranon from contact with the left-front interior door panel. He sustained a left distal supracondylar femur fracture from contact with the knee bolster. He also sustained fractures of the left proximal tibia and fibula from contact with the left-front kickpanel.
